Design Chess Game

Make Move (b1 -> b2)
Step 1 : Check if this move is valid (check if b2 contains same color piece)
Step 2 : Will current player under attack after this
Step 3 : Check if b2 contains a piece  collect it
Step 4 : If piece moved a pawn and b2 is last row if yes promote it to Queen / Kight / Bishop
Step 5 : Is this a castling move
Step 6 : Does this move result in checkmate


Common : b2 cell must not contain same colour piece

King Make Move : abs(x1-x2) + abs(y1-y2) == 1
if(x < 2 && y < 2 && x+y > 0 ) {
           return true;
       }
Castling Move :

Queen : Bishop + Rock

Bishop : abs(x1-x2) == abs(y1-y2)

Rock : x1 == x2 || y1 == y1

Knight : abs(x1-x2) * abs(y1-y2) == 2

Pawn : 1 / 2 / cross

